0financial%20meltdown%20if%20passed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20in%20Congress%20are%20trying%20to%20extend%20a%20winning%20streak%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrypto-week-congress-stablecoins-genius-act-clarity-bitcoin-record-high-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecrypto%20legislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20kicked%20off%20last%20month%2C%20but%20Democrats%20are%20ringing%20more%20alarm%20bells%20over%20the%20latest%20proposed%20bill.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20a%20group%20of%20Senate%20Republicans%20introduced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.banking.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fsenate_banking_committee_digital_asset_market_structure_legislation_discussion_draft.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edraft%20discussion%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Responsible%20Financial%20Innovation%20Act%20of%202025%20(RFIA).%20It%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F118th-congress%2Fsenate-bill%2F2281%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%20by%20Senators%20Cynthia%20Lummis%20and%20Kirsten%20Gillibrand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20seeks%20to%20build%20on%20the%20recently%20passed%20CLARITY%20Act%2C%20which%20establishes%20a%20regulatory%20framework%20for%20digital%20assets.%20However%2C%20the%20Senate%20Committee%20on%20Banking%2C%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Affairs'%20democratic%20staff%20recently%20released%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.banking.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fbhua_rfia_dem_staff_analysis.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efact%20sheet%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20bill%2C%20laying%20out%20key%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20stark%20contrast%20to%20Republican%20lawmakers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrypto-stablecoins-how-to-invest-trump-genius-act-btc-eth-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewho%20have%20touted%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20economic%20benefits%20of%20crypto%2C%20Democrats%20see%20it%20as%20potentially%20destabilizing%20and%20riddled%20with%20potential%20conflicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20from%20Democrats%20on%20the%20Senate%20Banking%20Committee%2C%20lawmakers%20flagged%20risks%20to%20Americans'%20retirement%20savings%2C%20which%20they%20say%20are%20created%20by%20compromising%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission's%20authority%20to%20regulate%20the%20sector%2C%20instead%2C%20assigning%20responsibility%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bchronically%20under-resourced%20CFTC.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20concerningly%2C%20the%20bill%20provides%20a%20superhighway%20for%20traditional%20assets%20to%20escape%20the%20SEC's%20authority%20simply%20by%20converting%20stocks%20and%20other%20non-crypto%20securities%20into%20tokens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20says%20that%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20would%20use%20the%20concept%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Bancillary%20asset%2C%26quot%3B%20allowing%20companies%20to%20sell%20crypto%20to%20investors%20without%20the%20protections%20under%20securities%20law.%20Sellers%20could%20%26quot%3Bself-certify%2C%26quot%3B%20avoiding%20the%20SEC%20oversight%20meant%20to%20protect%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20for%20Americans%20who%20invest%20in%20non-crypto%20companies%2C%20this%20would%20mean%20exposing%20their%20retirement%20accounts%20and%20investments%20to%20greater%20volatility%20while%20stripping%20away%20existing%20federal%20and%20state%20enforcement%20tools%20to%20protect%20and%20help%20investors%20who%20get%20scammed.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20argue%20that%20the%20bill%20raises%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bfinancial%20meltdown%26quot%3B%20as%20FDIC-insured%20institutions%20engage%20with%20crypto%20and%20are%20exposed%20to%20its%20risks.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bill%20would%20bring%20crypto%20activities%20firmly%20within%20the%20taxpayer%20safety%20net%2C%20threatening%20the%20Deposit%20Insurance%20Fund%2C%20the%20safety%20and%20soundness%20of%20the%20banking%20system%2C%20and%20the%20ongoing%20availability%20of%20the%20critical%20non-crypto%20banking%20services%20that%20businesses%20and%20households%20rely%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20the%20committee's%20ranking%20member%2C%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.banking.senate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fminority%2Fat-hearing-ranking-member-warren-releases-principles-for-crypto-market-structure-legislation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoutlined%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0the%20principles%20she%20believes%3C%2Fspan%3E%20are%20necessary%20to%20establish%20a%20crypto%20market%20framework%20that%20effectively%20regulates%20the%20market.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Lummis%20defended%20the%20proposed%20bill.%20In%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20she%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAncillary%20assets%20draw%20the%20clearest%20legal%20line%20between%20securities%20and%20commodities%20and%20provide%20consumers%20with%20the%20disclosures%20they%20need%20to%20make%20informed%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrypto-legislation-regulation-rfia-warren-lummis-gillibrand-sec-cftc-meltdown-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755028520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b9284cfc04e97619b4898%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrypto-legislation-regulation-rfia-warren-lummis-gillibrand-sec-cftc-meltdown-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Senate%20Democrats%20published%20a%20letter%20sounding%20the%20alarm%20over%20risks%20to%20financial%20stability%20posed%20by%20a%20bill%20aimed%20at%20restructuring%20regulation%20of%20the%20sector.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A121%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3