n%20to%20her%20daughter's%20assistance%20when%20she%20heard%20her%20scream.%20In%20the%20aftermath%2C%20neither%20Hodges%20nor%20her%20mother%20knew%20what%20had%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20she%20knew%20is%20that%20something%20had%20hit%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20found%20the%20meteorite%2C%20this%20big%20rock%2C%20and%20they%20couldn't%20figure%20out%20how%20it%20had%20got%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt%20weighed%20around%208.5%20pounds.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221002%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hodges%20Meteorite%20%20%20recent.JPG%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef256494dca6813c2146995%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22751%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EUniversity%20of%20Alabama%20Museums%2C%20Tuscaloosa%2C%20Alabama%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EProndzinski%20said%20the%20meteorite%20is%20a%20chondrite%20or%20stony%20meteorite%20and%20composed%20of%20iron%20and%20nickel.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fsmithsonian-institution%2F1954-extraterrestrial-bruiser-shocked-alabama-woman-180973646%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmithsonian%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20meteorite%20is%20an%20estimated%204.5%20billion%20years%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20meteor%20entered%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20it%20broke%20apart.%20One%20fragment%20hit%20Hodges%20while%20another%20was%20located%20a%20few%20miles%20away.%20A%20farmer%2C%20Julius%20Kempis%20McKinney%2C%20discovered%20the%20second%20fragment%20while%20driving%20a%20mule-drawn%20wagon%20and%20later%20sold%20it%20for%20enough%20money%20to%20buy%20both%20a%20house%20and%20car%2C%20the%20Decatur%20Daily%20reported.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ENeighbors%20and%20law%20enforcement%20rushed%20to%20Ann%20Hodges'%20home.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224266%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mayor%20Ed%20J.%20Howard%2C%20Mrs.%20Hodges%2C%20Police%20Chief%20W.D.%20Ashcraft%20looking%20at%20ceiling%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b64cbcfc04e97619b42be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225353%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20University%20of%20Alabama%20Museums%2C%20Tuscaloosa%2C%20Alabama%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20you%20knew%20it%2C%20everyone%20in%20town%20was%20surrounding%20the%20house%20wanting%20to%20see%20what%20had%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20those%20days%20they%20didn't%20have%20Facebook%2C%20but%20word%20still%20traveled%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20doctor%20and%20the%20police%20were%20called%20to%20the%20home.%C2%A0Prondzinski%20said%20it%20was%20Mayor%20Ed%20Howard%20and%20the%20police%20chief%20who%20discovered%20the%20hole%20in%20the%20ceiling%20where%20the%20meteorite%20had%20crashed%20through.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Decatur%20Daily%20reported%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20meteorite%20left%20a%20large%20%26quot%3Bgrapefruit%26quot%3B-sized%20bruise%20on%20Hodges'%20hip.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223386%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anne%20Hodges%20after%20being%20hit%20by%20a%20meteorite%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef21132f34d0509447f2aa3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222540%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJay%20Leviton%2FThe%20LIFE%20Images%20Collection%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20had%20this%20incredible%20bruise%20on%20her%20hip%2C%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BShe%20was%20taken%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20not%20because%20she%20was%20so%20severely%20injured%20that%20she%20needed%20to%20be%20hospitalized%2C%20but%20because%20she%20was%20very%20distraught%20by%20the%20whole%20incident.%20She%20was%20a%20very%20nervous%20person%2C%20and%20she%20didn't%20like%20all%20the%20notoriety%20or%20all%20the%20people%20around.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHodges'%20husband%2C%20Eugene%2C%20arrived%20home%20from%20work%20to%20find%20his%20house%20surrounded%20by%20a%20crowd%20of%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHodges'%20radio%20may%20have%20saved%20her%20from%20being%20seriously%20injured.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222778%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ann%20Hodges%20points%20to%20a%20hole%20in%20her%20ceiling%20where%20a%20meteorite%20crashed%20through%20before%20hitting%20her.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b6479194a2d49b8ae6985%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20meteorite%20bounced%20off%20the%20radio%2C%20pictured.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FBettmann%20Archive%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20it%20came%20through%20the%20roof%2C%20that%20slowed%20its%20trajectory%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20did%20bounce%20off%20the%20radio%20%E2%80%94%20if%20she%20had%20been%20lying%20under%20the%20radio%2C%20it%20would%20have%20broken%20her%20leg%20or%20her%20back.%20It%20probably%20wouldn't%20have%20killed%20her%2C%20but%20it%20would%20have%20done%20a%20lot%20more%20damage%20to%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Air%20Force%20confiscated%20the%20meteorite%20so%20they%20could%20determine%20its%20origin.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223348%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Airforce%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef211e4aee6a85fba013193%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222511%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Air%20Force%20looked%20at%20it%20because%20they%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20flying%20saucer%20and%20all%20this%20other%20wild%20and%20crazy%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20it%20was%20confirmed%20a%20meteorite%2C%20the%20Hodgeses%20faced%20a%20lengthy%20litigation%20process%20to%20acquire%20ownership%20of%20it.%20Their%20landlord%2C%20Birdie%20Guy%2C%20believe%20the%20meteorite%20belonged%20to%20her%20because%20she%20owned%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuing%20is%20the%20only%20way%20she'll%20ever%20get%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Hodges%20told%20reporters%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20God%20intended%20it%20for%20me.%20After%20all%2C%20it%20hit%20me!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Farchive.decaturdaily.com%2Fdecaturdaily%2Fnews%2F061130%2Fmeteorite.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Decatur%20Daily%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20Guy%20wanted%20money%20to%20fix%20the%20house's%20roof.%20Litigation%20went%20on%20for%20a%20year%2C%20and%20Prondzinski%20said%20Guy%20settled%20the%20case%20for%20%24500.%20The%20house%20eventually%20caught%20fire%20and%20was%20demolished%20to%20make%20way%20for%20a%20mobile%20home%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHodges%20became%20an%20overnight%20celebrity%20and%20was%20even%20featured%20on%20a%20game%20show.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222097%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22I've%20Got%20a%20Secret%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef3a02419182419ad5f580d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221573%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECBS%20Photo%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20became%20famous%20for%2015%20minutes.%20She%20had%20all%20these%20photo%20shoots.%20She%20was%20invited%20to%20go%20to%20New%20York%20City%20to%20be%20on%20Garry%20Moore's%20show%20'%5B%26quot%3BI've%20Got%20a%20Secret%26quot%3B%5D%20where%20the%20panel%20had%20to%20guess%20what's%20her%20profession%20or%20what%20happened%20to%20her%2C%20why%20she%20is%20a%20notable%20figure%2C%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHodges%20would%20receive%20fan%20mail%20from%20churches%2C%20children%2C%20and%20educators%20asking%20about%20the%20meteorite%2C%20but%20she%20never%20answered%20any%20of%20them%2C%20leaving%20it%20to%20her%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20was%20a%20very%20quiet%20person.%20She%20was%20a%20very%20private%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20did%20not%20like%20having%20all%20the%20notoriety.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHodges%20decided%20to%20donate%20the%20meteorite%20to%20the%20Alabama%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20History.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22869%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20day%20a%20meteorite%20hit%20a%20sylacauga%20woman%20ae8cb90f087e5e4d%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef257f23f737024d040fc2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22651%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20University%20of%20Alabama%20Museums%2C%20Tuscaloosa%2C%20Alabama%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20time%20she%20had%20got%20the%20meteorite%20in%20her%20possession%2C%20she%20was%20so%20sick%20of%20the%20whole%20thing.%20She%20said%2C%20'You%20can%20have%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Prondzinski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20Hodges%20asked%20in%20return%20was%20for%20the%20museum%20to%20reimburse%20her%20for%20her%20attorney%20fees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProndzinski%20said%20the%20meteorite%20created%20problems%20between%20Hodges%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Eugene.%20Her%20husband%20wanted%20to%20make%20money%20off%20the%20meteorite%20but%20failed%20to%20secure%20a%20buyer.%20The%20two%20eventually%20divorced%20in%201964.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201972%2C%20aged%2052%2C%20Hodges%20died%20of%20kidney%20failure%20in%20a%20nursing%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHodges%20is%20the%20first%20documented%20person%20to%20have%20been%20hit%20by%20a%20meteorite.%20Recently%2C%20a%20man%20in%20Georgia%20narrowly%20missed%20being%20hit%20by%20another.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22This%20meteorite%20landed