ed%20like%20a%20gunshot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20suspect%20that%20he%20heard%20three%20simultaneous%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Scott%20Harris%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia's%20Franklin%20College%20of%20Arts%20and%20Sciences'%20department%20of%20geology%2C%20the%20university%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.uga.edu%2Fuga-names-new-meteorite%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BOne%20was%20the%20collision%20with%20his%20roof%2C%20one%20was%20a%20tiny%20cone%20of%20a%20sonic%20boom%20and%20a%20third%20was%20it%20impacting%20the%20floor%20all%20in%20the%20same%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20enough%20energy%20when%20it%20hit%20the%20floor%20that%20it%20pulverized%20part%20of%20the%20material%20down%20to%20literal%20dust%20fragments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20studied%20the%20rocks%20and%20concluded%20the%20meteorite%20could%20have%20formed%204.56%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20making%20it%20older%20than%20the%20Earth.%20It%20is%20still%20being%20studied%20at%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEvery%20day%2C%20Earth%20is%20hit%20with%20more%20than%20100%20tons%20of%20space%20dust%20and%20debris.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225342%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Meteor%20Crater%20in%20Arizona%20is%20almost%20a%20mile%20wide.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b66a9194a2d49b8ae69e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223561%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeteor%20Crater%20in%20Arizona%20is%20almost%20a%20mile%20wide.%3Cp%3E%3A%20Marli%20Miller%2FUCG%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fmission_pages%2Fasteroids%2Foverview%2Ffastfacts.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20about%20once%20a%20year%20a%20car-sized%20asteroid%20enters%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20but%20burns%20up%20before%20it%20can%20touch%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20expert%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fhow-many-meteorites-hit-earth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20for%20sure%20how%20many%20asteroids%20hit%20Earth%20each%20year%2C%20he%20estimated%20%26quot%3Babout%206%2C100%20meteorite%20falls%20per%20year%20over%20the%20entire%20Earth%2C%20and%20about%201%2C800%20over%20the%20land.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20these%20go%20undetected%2C%20but%20occasionally%20they'll%20capture%20the%20public's%20attention%2C%20like%20Hodges'%20meteorite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20in%201992%20a%2026-pound%20meteorite%20landed%20on%20a%20red%20Chevy%20Malibu%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20in%202013%2C%20one%20exploded%20over%20Russia.%20There%20has%20also%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fearliest-evidence-meteorite-killed-person.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20meteorite%20killing%20a%20man%20and%20injuring%20another%20in%201888.%20Meteor%20Crater%2C%20which%20is%20almost%20a%20mile%20wide%2C%20in%20Arizona%20shows%20the%20impact%20a%20large%20meteorite%20can%20have.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProndzinski%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20in%20the%20years%20since%20Hodges%20was%20struck%2C%20her%20story%20remains%20popular%2C%20and%20people%20have%20contacted%20the%20museum%20about%20using%20the%20story%20in%20movies%2C%20plays%2C%20and%20even%20a%20graphic%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falabama-woman-first-person-hit-by-a-meteorite-2020-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755016305000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b6b49cfc04e97619b43ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fala